You are given an integer array arr[]. You need to create an ArrayList of objects of class ArrItem and then you have to sort this ArrayList by the first field. The sorting has to be done in increasing order. If the item field clashes then sort by index field in increasing order.

Examples:

Input: arr[] = [5, 5, 4, 3, 2, 5]
Output: (2,4) (3,3) (4,2) (5,0) (5,1) (5,5)
Explanation: Elements are sorted in increasing order and are printed in the format (item, index).
Input: arr[] = [8, 5, 99, 1]
Output: (1,3) (5,1) (8,0) (99,2)
Explanation: Elements are sorted in increasing order and are printed in the format (item, index).
Constraints:
1 ≤ arr.length ≤ 103

// User function Template for Java

/*
class ArrItem
{
    public int item;
    public int index;

    public ArrItem(int item,int index)
    {
        this.item=item;
        this.index=index;
    }
}
*/

class Sorting {
    public ArrayList<ArrItem> sortedWithIndices(int arr[]) {
        // Your code here
        ArrayList<ArrItem> list = new ArrayList<>();
        for(int i=0; i<arr.length; i++){
            list.add(new ArrItem(arr[i],i));
        }
        list.sort(Comparator.comparingInt((ArrItem a)-> a.item).thenComparingInt(a->a.index));
        return list;
        // Create an array of ArrItem objects and sort by item field
    }
}
